Date: Mon, 25 Aug 2014 13:14:03 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1044/1587] ARM: DRA7: hwmod: Fix RNG hwmod flags

RNG doesn't support module smart-idle wakeup/smart-idle property.
Currently hwmod is setting it to smart-idle, which RNG doesn't support
and giving the folllwong warning while idling:
[    0.197727] omap_hwmod: rng: _wait_target_disable failed
So enable HWMOD_SWSUP_SIDLE flag to not rely on module's smart-idle
mode.

Signed-off-by: Lokesh Vutla <lokeshvutla@ti.com>
[zou: Original patch taken from
ti-sdk-am335x-evm-08.00.00.00-Linux-x86-Install.bin]
Signed-off-by: Cao Zou <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
index 3ace51a..030b261 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_hwmod_7xx_data.c
@@ -2207,6 +2207,7 @@ static struct omap_hwmod_class dra7xx_rng_hwmod_class = {
 static struct omap_hwmod dra7xx_rng_hwmod = {
 	.name           = "rng",
 	.class          = &dra7xx_rng_hwmod_class,
+	.flags		= HWMOD_SWSUP_SIDLE,
 	.clkdm_name     = "l4sec_clkdm",
 	.prcm = {
 		.omap4 = {
